caption.text:
First of all, i want to thank God for his blessing that i amazingly managed to watch my very first concert (even with a strong objection from my parents) and even got a very front queue number (luckily the qn works) 🙏
And i want to thank @lizanatallia (as the host of this GA) for giving me the chance to recall and carefully consider which was the most memorable moment of exoluxioninjkt.

My best moment was 'My Answer' stage. I've been madly in love with this song since it was released in April last year. I even looked up for the piano partiture online and have been practicing for 10 months consecutively. This song made me started to learn piano again dilligently and given me the strength whenever i'm having a bad day at school back in my senior year days :") This song is a perfect combination between Baek, Dyo and Suho's made-in-heaven vocal + Baekhyun's superb piano skill. Since Baek is on the top of my bias list,having the chance to listening to it LIVE was kind of bewitching 😍. His voice was too real and his piano performance really took my breath away!!! 😢😢😢 i couldn't believe it happened and nearly cried back then. REALLY.

The things i regret were my section was far far away from the main stage, the stage was high and ICE's pole had blocked my sight from seeing the screen infront. I even forget to record this moment oh my god -___-. In the end i enjoyed this performance ONLY through my ears and my heart 😌. But those were okay though, since a song may give a thousand meaning to those who cherish it 💕 *a little story about my concert props : D.O was actually rank #3rd on my bias list, but i ended up getting some of his fansupport rather than Baek since 2 of my friend was his hard shipper and i followed them around looking for fansupports lol So yeah in the end i didn't get any Baek pc as i've been aiming for. 
#EXOLUXIONINA #EXOLUXIONJKT #EXOGAbyLIZA

"Don't cry because it's over, smile because it happened."
Dr. Seuss

My first time watching a live concert was such a wonderful experince. Seeing you guys in real life was wanjeon dalla than seeing you on TVs or MVs 😢 Too bad it ended so soon, too sad it happened so fast until i couldn't even captured it in my memory😭😭😭 well yea i still wanna cry #baper "Terima kasih EXO", 우리는 다음 콘서트에서 꼭 (꼭!!!) 다시만나요! 나는 당신을 기다릴게요!

#exoluxionina #exoluxionjkt

ODHA (Orang Dengan HIV AIDS) is a person who got infected by human immunodeficiency virus. This virus is a blood-borne virus which is transmitted via sexual intercourse, shared intravenous drug, and mother-to-child transmission.
This virus will not be transmitted just by touching the ODHA.
So, WE should remove the stigma about discriminating people with HIV/AIDS and give them our love and empathy, not discrimination and hate.

Today, 1st of December is World HIV/AIDS day.
I, Veronica Nadya, so proud of joining all Ambassador of Public Health of AMSA-Indonesia to share this fact.
